.description
Implementation of the Oberon V4 operationg system, like it was designed together
with the programing language Oberon among others by Prof. Niklaus Wirth.\n\n
The system represents a modern operating system with multitasking, graphical
user interface and an Oberon-2 compiler. Special features are object oriented
programming concept, dynamic loading, garbage collector, extensibility and a
enlarged meaning of text.\n
A text editor, a drawing tool and a Minesweeper game are included.\n\n
Source code designed with the system can be used at every implementation without
changes. Implementations are available for Mac, Power-Mac,
IBM-RS6000, Windows, SGI, Sun, Linux, DecStation, ....
